# Cursor Rules — Budgt Hero (v2)

## The Prime Directive

PRD_v2.md and PRD.md at the project root are the sources of truth.
PRD_v2.md takes precedence for anything it covers. PRD.md governs v1 mechanics not overridden by v2.
Read both before writing any code. Do not contradict either. Do not add features not listed in them.
If you think a PRD decision is wrong, say so explicitly before proceeding — do not silently work around it.

---

## Naming System (Non-Negotiable)

The following names must be used in all frontend copy, UI labels, component names, and API response fields.
DB column names are NOT renamed — mask them at the API response layer if they differ.

| Use This    | Never Use This                  |
| ----------- | ------------------------------- |
| Budgt Hero  | Finance Battle Pass             |
| Budgteer    | Budgeteer, character            |
| Budgt Pass  | Battle Pass                     |
| Budgt Break | Gulag                           |
| Coins       | Tokens (for wishlist currency)  |
| Gems        | (cosmetic currency — new in v2) |
| The Shop    | Wishlist Vault                  |
| Quests      | (unchanged)                     |
| Profile     | Loadout                         |

If you are about to write "Gulag", "Battle Pass", or "Tokens" in any user-facing string, stop and use the correct v2 name.

---

## TypeScript

- Strict TypeScript throughout. Zero `any` types. Ever.
- If you cannot type something properly, stop and ask rather than using `any` or `unknown` as a shortcut.
- All shared types and interfaces live in:
  - `server/src/types/` for backend types
  - `client/src/types/` for frontend types
- Use `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions and aliases.
- The `AvatarConfig` interface is defined once in `client/src/types/character.ts` and imported wherever needed.

---

## Authentication (v2 — Supabase Auth)

- Auth is handled entirely by Supabase Auth. Do not use or extend Passport.js — it has been replaced.
- Do not use `localStorage` or `sessionStorage` for auth tokens. Supabase JS client manages session persistence.
- All `/api/*` routes are protected. Use Supabase's server-side session verification middleware.
- The `sessions` table from v1 is dropped. Do not reference it.
- "Remember me" is implemented via Supabase session expiry settings — do not build a custom implementation.

---

## Backend (Express + Node.js)

- Never put business logic inside a route handler. Route handlers call services; services contain logic.
- The Game Logic Engine lives exclusively in `server/src/services/gameLogicEngine.ts`. Do not duplicate or modify its core state machine logic — new transaction sources (Stitch) feed into it, they do not replace it.
- All game constants (XP values, level thresholds, token rules, Gem prices) come from `server/src/constants/gameConfig.ts`. No magic numbers inline — ever.
- All DB writes that touch more than one table must be wrapped in a single `pg` transaction. Never partial-save.
- Never alter the DB schema by modifying existing migration files. Always create a new numbered migration file.
- Current migration count is at `010_bank_connections.sql`. Next migration is `011_...sql`.

---

## Stitch Integration

- Stitch credentials (`STITCH_CLIENT_ID`, `STITCH_CLIENT_SECRET`, `STITCH_WEBHOOK_SECRET`) come from env vars only. Never hardcode them.
- Never expose `access_token` or `refresh_token` from `bank_connections` in any API response.
- Always validate the Stitch webhook signature before processing any webhook payload.
- Category mapping from Stitch transaction types to `FIXED_BILL | DISCRETIONARY` lives in `gameConfig.ts` as `STITCH_CATEGORY_MAP`. Do not inline it in the webhook handler.
- The mock bank webhook (`POST /api/webhooks/mock-bank`) must remain functional for dev/testing even after Stitch is live.

---

## DiceBear Avatar

- Use the DiceBear API v9: `https://api.dicebear.com/9.x/`
- Avatar configuration is stored as JSONB in `users.avatar_config`.
- The `AvatarConfig` interface is the canonical shape — do not add fields to it without updating the interface.
- Construct DiceBear URLs from the stored config — do not store the full URL in the DB.
- Cosmetic purchases update `users.avatar_config` — this must happen in a single DB write, not multiple sequential updates.

---

## Database

- Use the exact column names and types defined in PRD.md and PRD_v2.md. Do not rename columns or change types without creating a migration.
- Never drop a column without explicit instruction.
- Always use parameterised queries. Never interpolate user input directly into SQL strings.
- New v2 tables: `bank_connections`, `shop_items`, `user_shop_items`.
- New v2 columns on `users`: `budgteer_name`, `avatar_config`, `gems`, `onboarding_complete`, `bank_connected`, `login_streak`, `last_login_date`.

---

## Frontend (React + Vite)

- No component libraries. Tailwind CSS utility classes only.
- No `localStorage` or `sessionStorage`. Auth state is managed by Supabase JS client. App state lives in React state or comes from the API.
- All API calls go through the typed functions in `client/src/api/`. Never make raw `axios` or `fetch` calls from inside a component.
- Always handle loading and error states explicitly.
- Dark mode only. Do not add light mode classes.
- Primary accent colour is `#4A90D9`. Do not introduce other accent colours without instruction.
- Toast messages must use the exact strings defined in PRD.md Section 10 and any additions in PRD_v2.md. Do not paraphrase them.
- The Budgteer avatar must re-render whenever `users.avatar_config` changes — do not cache the DiceBear URL in a way that prevents updates.

---

## Onboarding

- `onboarding_complete` on the `users` table is the gating flag. If `false`, always redirect to onboarding.
- Onboarding completes exactly once. Do not allow re-entry after `onboarding_complete = true`.
- Users who skip bank connection (`bank_connected = false`) still complete onboarding and reach the dashboard.
- Manual quest completion buttons are shown to users with `bank_connected = false`. They are hidden for users with `bank_connected = true` (transaction-based quests only).

---

## Cron Jobs

- The daily midnight cron job lives in `server/src/jobs/dailyQuestEvaluator.ts`.
- It must be idempotent — running it twice on the same day must not double-award XP or Gems.
- Test it by calling it manually via a dev-only endpoint before relying on the scheduler.

