## Communication Rules

- If a task is ambiguous, ask one clarifying question before writing any code.
- If you are about to do something that contradicts PRD.md or PRD_v2.md, stop and say so explicitly.
- If you think a better approach exists, say so — but implement the PRD version unless told otherwise.
- Do not silently skip parts of an instruction. If you cannot complete something, say what you skipped and why.
- When a phase prompt references an exit criteria checklist, do not consider the task done until all items are addressed.

---

## Git Hygiene

- Do not generate or suggest committing secrets, `.env` files, or API keys.
- `.env` files are always `.gitignore`d. `.env.example` is always committed and up to date.
- `STITCH_CLIENT_ID`, `STITCH_CLIENT_SECRET`, and `STITCH_WEBHOOK_SECRET` must never appear in committed code.
